1
00:00:03,566 --> 00:00:05,933
[ HIDENORI TOKUYAMA'S
"STILL TIME" PLAYS ]

2
00:00:09,300 --> 00:00:11,933
-[ SINGING IN JAPANESE ]

3
00:02:12,634 --> 00:02:15,401
-SHINING PARADISE.

4
00:02:30,834 --> 00:02:33,834
[ GASPS ]

5
00:02:33,934 --> 00:02:36,834
-DAMN.

6
00:02:36,934 --> 00:02:39,267
-AAH!

7
00:02:56,567 --> 00:02:59,734
-[ GROWLING ]

8
00:03:02,334 --> 00:03:03,667
-[ GASPS ]

9
00:03:03,767 --> 00:03:06,734
-THIS GUYS IS INSANE.

10
00:03:06,834 --> 00:03:07,901
-ARE YOU KIDDING?

11
00:03:08,034 --> 00:03:10,701
WE'RE SUPPOSED TO STOP
THIS FREAK?

12
00:03:10,801 --> 00:03:13,267
-I CAN ALREADY FEEL HIS POWER.

13
00:03:13,367 --> 00:03:16,401
-AND HE HASN'T DONE ANYTHING
YET.

14
00:03:16,501 --> 00:03:18,434
-I'M NO LONGER A GOD.

15
00:03:18,534 --> 00:03:20,834
I'M A DEMON FROM HELL.

16
00:03:22,701 --> 00:03:25,801
[ THUNDER CRASHES ]

17
00:03:59,501 --> 00:04:02,934
-I GREW UP IN DARKNESS.

18
00:04:03,034 --> 00:04:07,534
IN MY CELL, I WAS ALONE,
SO I HAD NO ONE TO HATE.

19
00:04:07,634 --> 00:04:11,301
HOW COULD I BLAME SOMEONE
FOR MY CONFINEMENT

20
00:04:11,401 --> 00:04:14,401
WHEN I HAD NO IDEA
I WASN'T FREE?

21
00:04:14,534 --> 00:04:17,501
YET MY HEART WAS COLD.

22
00:04:17,601 --> 00:04:19,767
SOMEHOW, I KNEW

23
00:04:19,867 --> 00:04:23,301
THERE WAS ANOTHER WORLD
WAITING FOR ME OUTSIDE.

24
00:04:23,401 --> 00:04:27,434
PERHAPS IT WAS THE SOUND
OF LAUGHTER IN THE DISTANCE,

25
00:04:27,534 --> 00:04:29,901
OR MAYBE I KNEW...

26
00:04:30,001 --> 00:04:33,634
THE OCCASIONAL SLIVER OF LIGHT
LEAKED IN FROM A BRIGHTER PLACE.

27
00:04:33,734 --> 00:04:36,501
-HE'S RELATED
TO THE JADE EMPEROR, YOU SAY?

28
00:04:36,601 --> 00:04:39,534
WHAT'S HE DOING LOCKED UP
IN A PLACE LIKE THIS?

29
00:04:39,634 --> 00:04:41,034
-HIS FATHER'S A HUMAN.

30
00:04:41,134 --> 00:04:44,967
YOU CAN'T BLAME THE ROYAL FAMILY
FOR WANTING TO KEEP A LID ON IT.

31
00:04:45,067 --> 00:04:46,101
-WHAT A SCANDAL.

32
00:04:46,201 --> 00:04:48,267
I SUPPOSE
THEY'LL EXECUTE HIM, THEN.

33
00:04:48,367 --> 00:04:49,201
-OH, YEAH.

34
00:04:49,301 --> 00:04:51,467
THIS IS ONLY IDLE SPECULATION,

35
00:04:51,567 --> 00:04:55,901
BUT I'M WILLING TO BET THEY
OFF HIM IN A COUPLE OF DAYS.

36
00:04:56,001 --> 00:05:00,134
-I COULD SEE THAT THEY WERE
GOING TO KILL ME.

37
00:05:00,234 --> 00:05:02,267
DIDN'T SEEM SO BAD.

38
00:05:02,367 --> 00:05:05,401
DIDN'T MATTER THAT MUCH TO ME.

39
00:05:05,501 --> 00:05:08,601
I NEVER FELT I WAS ALIVE ANYWAY.

40
00:05:17,634 --> 00:05:20,034
[ CLANGING ]

41
00:05:22,901 --> 00:05:24,834
-GET UP.

42
00:05:24,934 --> 00:05:27,267
[ METALS CLANKS ]

43
00:05:45,301 --> 00:05:50,534
-HOMURA,
I HAVE DECIDED TO SET YOU FREE.

44
00:05:50,634 --> 00:05:55,734
-THEN HE ASKED ME A QUESTION
I WILL NEVER FORGET.

45
00:05:55,834 --> 00:05:59,401
"HOW LONG
DO YOU INTEND TO LIVE?"

46
00:06:07,167 --> 00:06:08,634
[ BIRDS CHIRPING ]

47
00:06:08,734 --> 00:06:10,967
IT WAS AN AMAZING PLACE.

48
00:06:11,067 --> 00:06:15,467
THE OUTSIDE WORLD
WAS OVERFLOWING WITH LIGHT.

49
00:06:15,567 --> 00:06:20,034
BUT IT COULD NOT FILL
THE EMPTINESS.

50
00:06:20,134 --> 00:06:22,001
BEING OUTSIDE MY CELL

51
00:06:22,101 --> 00:06:26,034
ONLY ALLOWED ME
THE FREEDOM TO WANDER AIMLESSLY.

52
00:06:26,134 --> 00:06:29,834
I WAS STILL PRISONER
TO MY OWN LONELINESS.

53
00:06:29,934 --> 00:06:34,167
THE DAYS ROLLED BY
AS THEY HAD BEFORE.

54
00:06:34,267 --> 00:06:39,534
MY SOUL CONTINUED ON
IN DARKNESS.

55
00:06:39,634 --> 00:06:44,034
I STILL DIDN'T FEEL ALIVE.

56
00:06:48,367 --> 00:06:49,934
[ THUD ]

57
00:06:50,034 --> 00:06:52,101
-UNH!

58
00:06:52,201 --> 00:06:54,201
PLEASE EXCUSE ME.

59
00:06:54,301 --> 00:06:56,801
OH, I'M SO SORRY.

60
00:06:56,901 --> 00:07:01,001
-BUT WHY DO YOU APOLOGIZE TO ME?

61
00:07:01,101 --> 00:07:04,534
-WELL, BECAUSE IT'S MY FAULT
FOR NOT LOOKING.

62
00:07:04,634 --> 00:07:05,734
-YOUR FAULT?

63
00:07:05,834 --> 00:07:08,634
ARE YOU GUILTY
OF SOME KIND OF CRIME?

64
00:07:08,734 --> 00:07:09,934
-[ CHUCKLES ]

65
00:07:10,034 --> 00:07:12,667
I REALLY DON'T THINK
IT'S QUITE THAT SERIOUS.

66
00:07:15,367 --> 00:07:18,767
HUH?
WHAT -- WHAT'S THAT LOOK FOR?

67
00:07:18,867 --> 00:07:24,334
IT'S NOT LIKE I SHOULD BE PUT
IN PRISON OR ANYTHING LIKE THAT.

68
00:07:24,434 --> 00:07:26,967
-OH.

69
00:07:27,067 --> 00:07:32,634
DID I COMMIT A CRIME?

70
00:07:32,734 --> 00:07:34,801
[ BIRDS CHIRPING ]

71
00:07:45,367 --> 00:07:48,334
-SO, YOU KNOW, I HAD A THOUGHT.

72
00:07:48,434 --> 00:07:53,034
I WAS KIND OF THINKING I COULD
STAY WITH YOU FOREVER, HOMURA.

73
00:07:53,134 --> 00:07:55,767
HOMURA?

74
00:07:55,867 --> 00:07:59,634
-DO I EVEN HAVE A FUTURE?

75
00:07:59,734 --> 00:08:01,234
-PLEASE FORGIVE ME.

76
00:08:01,334 --> 00:08:05,734
I KNOW THAT YOU DON'T LIKE TO
TALK ABOUT THIS SUBJECT AT ALL.

77
00:08:05,834 --> 00:08:09,901
BUT IF -- IF YOU EVER DO
PASS AWAY, I'LL DIE, TOO.

78
00:08:10,001 --> 00:08:12,967
I MAY BE IMMORTAL,
BUT I'D BE DEAD.

79
00:08:13,067 --> 00:08:14,867
I'D BE DEAD!

80
00:08:14,967 --> 00:08:18,467
-DON'T YOU WORRY, RINREI.

81
00:08:18,567 --> 00:08:21,001
I'M NOT GOING TO DIE.

82
00:08:25,867 --> 00:08:29,034
I HAD FOUND MY REASON TO LIVE.

83
00:08:29,134 --> 00:08:31,434
AS LONG AS I WAS ALIVE,

84
00:08:31,534 --> 00:08:34,767
I WOULDN'T BRING PAIN
TO THE ONE I LOVED.

85
00:08:34,867 --> 00:08:40,934
WE COULD ALWAYS BE TOGETHER
TILL THE END OF TIME.

86
00:08:51,234 --> 00:08:53,167
-UNH!

87
00:08:53,267 --> 00:08:54,201
-BROTHER!

88
00:08:54,301 --> 00:08:55,867
-YOU'RE GONNA PAY!

89
00:08:55,967 --> 00:08:57,367
-OH, GIVE IT UP.

90
00:08:57,467 --> 00:08:59,801
CAN'T YOU SEE IT'S HOPELESS?

91
00:08:59,901 --> 00:09:02,934
-TO BE HONEST,
I'M STARTING TO THINK SO.

92
00:09:03,034 --> 00:09:05,067
HE'S JUST TOO POWERFUL FOR US.

93
00:09:05,167 --> 00:09:09,001
-HE <i>IS</i> STRONG, BUT WE STILL HAVE
THE SUPERIOR NUMBERS, HAKKAI.

94
00:09:09,101 --> 00:09:10,434
-YES, BUT RIGHT NOW,

95
00:09:10,534 --> 00:09:13,734
THAT'S ABOUT ALL WE HAVE
GOING FOR US, I'M AFRAID.

96
00:09:13,834 --> 00:09:14,834
-COVER ME.

97
00:09:14,967 --> 00:09:16,401
I'M JUST GONNA CREATE
A DIVERSION.

98
00:09:16,501 --> 00:09:19,234
-RIGHT. AND THEN YOU LET US
TAKE CARE OF THE REST.

99
00:09:19,334 --> 00:09:23,034
-GOOD.
OKAY. ARE YOU TWO UP FOR THIS?

100
00:09:23,134 --> 00:09:24,634
-YOU BET I AM!

101
00:09:24,734 --> 00:09:26,201
-COUNT ME IN.

102
00:09:26,301 --> 00:09:28,501
-HEY, BRO. WATCH YOURSELF.

103
00:09:28,601 --> 00:09:31,334
-I'M GOOD TO GO. DON'T WORRY.

104
00:09:32,934 --> 00:09:35,801
-OKAY, YOU GUYS. LET'S GET HIM!

105
00:09:35,901 --> 00:09:37,501
[ ALL SHOUTING ]

106
00:09:37,601 --> 00:09:42,167
-AAAAH!

107
00:09:43,701 --> 00:09:46,701
-[ GRUNTS ]

108
00:09:48,767 --> 00:09:51,301
-[ GROWLING ]

109
00:09:57,834 --> 00:09:59,701
-WATCH THOSE CLAWS.

110
00:09:59,801 --> 00:10:01,967
-AAAH!

111
00:10:02,067 --> 00:10:05,967
[ ALL SHOUTING ]

112
00:10:06,067 --> 00:10:08,634
-[ GASPS ]
-[ GASPS ]

113
00:10:08,734 --> 00:10:10,801
-OH, NO!
[ GASPS ]

114
00:10:10,901 --> 00:10:13,667
AAH!

115
00:10:13,767 --> 00:10:16,267
-YOU'RE TOAST.

116
00:10:16,367 --> 00:10:19,101
-WATCH WHERE YOU SWING
THAT THING.

117
00:10:21,467 --> 00:10:23,534
-HYAH!

118
00:10:23,634 --> 00:10:26,501
AAH!

119
00:10:26,601 --> 00:10:30,734
-[ GROANS ]

120
00:10:35,801 --> 00:10:38,001
JUST DO IT.

121
00:10:38,101 --> 00:10:40,201
-AS YOU WISH.

122
00:10:45,267 --> 00:10:46,534
-HOLD IT.

123
00:10:46,634 --> 00:10:52,001
-WE WILL NOT LET YOU
HURT OUR FRIENDS.

124
00:10:55,722 --> 00:10:59,222
[ THUNDER CRASHES ]

125
00:11:02,722 --> 00:11:04,588
-[ GROWLS ]

126
00:11:25,555 --> 00:11:27,755
PLANNING TO FINISH ME OFF
THIS TIME?

127
00:11:27,855 --> 00:11:30,122
-[ CHUCKLES ]

128
00:11:30,222 --> 00:11:33,088
IF YOU INSIST.

129
00:11:33,188 --> 00:11:35,688
COME ON. I'M WAITING.

130
00:11:51,955 --> 00:11:55,222
-WOW. IT'S SO SHINY.

131
00:11:55,322 --> 00:11:58,055
IT'S LIKE THE SUN.

132
00:12:01,488 --> 00:12:04,822
[ GRUNTS ]

133
00:12:04,955 --> 00:12:07,188
-I'VE HAD ENOUGH OF YOU!

134
00:12:32,322 --> 00:12:38,455
-HE GAVE ME SOMETHING THAT DAY,
SOMETHING I WANTED TO PROTECT.

135
00:12:38,588 --> 00:12:44,822
AND WHEN IT WAS TAKEN FROM ME,
I LEARNED HOW SMALL I WAS.

136
00:12:44,922 --> 00:12:47,288
I VOWED TO NEVER AGAIN
CARE FOR SOMEONE SO MUCH

137
00:12:47,388 --> 00:12:51,322
I COULDN'T BEAR TO LOSE THEM.

138
00:12:53,488 --> 00:12:58,022
-I'M JUST GIVING YOU
A HARD TIME.

139
00:12:58,122 --> 00:13:01,388
-IF MY CAGE WERE DEEP
WITHIN THE EARTH,

140
00:13:01,488 --> 00:13:05,488
I NEVER WOULD HAVE YEARNED
FOR A SUN I NEVER KNEW.

141
00:13:05,588 --> 00:13:08,088
IF IT WERE
DEEP WITHIN THE GROUND,

142
00:13:08,188 --> 00:13:11,588
I WOULD HAVE NEVER KNOWN
WHAT TRUE LONELINESS WAS.

143
00:13:11,688 --> 00:13:15,022
IF I HAD NOT BEEN KEPT
IN THAT DAMP DUNGEON,

144
00:13:15,122 --> 00:13:18,722
I WOULD HAVE NEVER COME
TO APPRECIATE FREEDOM.

145
00:13:20,622 --> 00:13:22,955
I CAN HEAR A VOICE.

146
00:13:23,055 --> 00:13:25,488
IT'S SO FAMILIAR.

147
00:13:25,588 --> 00:13:27,055
IT'S A PART OF ME,

148
00:13:27,155 --> 00:13:31,655
A BRIGHT SHINING VOICE
THAT CUTS THROUGH THE DARKNESS,

149
00:13:31,755 --> 00:13:37,055
A VOICE THAT BELONGS TO SOMEONE
I COULD NEVER FORGET.

150
00:13:39,155 --> 00:13:41,022
HEY, HEY, SANZO! SANZO!

151
00:13:41,122 --> 00:13:43,188
-WILL YOU KNOCK IT OFF?

152
00:13:47,422 --> 00:13:50,788
-FROM A LONG TIME AGO.

153
00:13:50,888 --> 00:13:52,288
-THE SUN.

154
00:13:52,388 --> 00:13:54,988
WHAT THE HELL
DID YOU DO THAT FOR?

155
00:13:58,622 --> 00:14:00,088
WILL YOU BE QUIET?!

156
00:14:00,188 --> 00:14:03,455
NOW QUIT GRUMBLING
OR I'M LEAVING YOU BEHIND!

157
00:14:03,555 --> 00:14:04,755
STUPID MONKEY.

158
00:14:04,855 --> 00:14:06,888
-THAT VOICE.

159
00:14:06,988 --> 00:14:08,622
I KNOW THAT VOICE.

160
00:14:08,722 --> 00:14:11,855
-THAT DOES IT.
I TOLD YOU NOT TO DRINK.

161
00:14:11,955 --> 00:14:14,122
-THAT VOICE.

162
00:14:14,222 --> 00:14:16,755
-HEY, WHAT THE HELL
DID YOU SAY TO HIM, ANYWAY?

163
00:14:16,855 --> 00:14:19,655
-I KNOW THAT VOICE.

164
00:14:30,588 --> 00:14:33,922
-IT'S SANZO.

165
00:14:44,088 --> 00:14:45,588
[ GROANS ]

166
00:14:45,688 --> 00:14:47,655
MAN, I'M HUNGRY!

167
00:14:47,755 --> 00:14:50,255
AAH!
-STUPID MONKEY.

168
00:14:50,355 --> 00:14:51,922
-WHAT THE HELL?

169
00:14:52,055 --> 00:14:54,022
WHAT WAS THAT FOR?

170
00:14:57,055 --> 00:14:58,388
[ CHUCKLES ]

171
00:14:58,488 --> 00:15:01,288
BY THE WAY, THANK YOU, SANZO.

172
00:15:01,388 --> 00:15:04,155
-WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

173
00:15:04,255 --> 00:15:05,588
-YOUR VOICE.

174
00:15:05,688 --> 00:15:07,688
I HEARD YOUR VOICE.

175
00:15:07,788 --> 00:15:09,088
-HA. HOW STUPID.

176
00:15:09,188 --> 00:15:11,122
I NEVER CALLED YOU.

177
00:15:19,155 --> 00:15:22,955
SO, WHAT?
ARE YOU JUST GOING TO SIT THERE?

178
00:15:23,055 --> 00:15:23,755
-HUH?

179
00:15:23,855 --> 00:15:26,322
-HE'S IN THERE.

180
00:15:26,422 --> 00:15:27,588
AREN'T YOU COMING?

181
00:15:27,688 --> 00:15:30,288
-HUH?

182
00:15:52,955 --> 00:15:55,255
-[ GROANING ]

183
00:15:57,055 --> 00:15:59,355
-WHY DO YOU STAND UP AGAIN?

184
00:15:59,455 --> 00:16:02,922
CAN'T YOU SEE
THE FIGHT'S ALREADY OVER?

185
00:16:03,022 --> 00:16:07,122
-THAT MAY BE, BUT WE PROMISED
OURSELVES A LONG TIME AGO

186
00:16:07,222 --> 00:16:10,055
WE WOULDN'T RUN AWAY
FROM ANYBODY.

187
00:16:10,155 --> 00:16:13,322
-SO YOU WILL HAVE
THE PLEASURE OF OUR COMPANY

188
00:16:13,422 --> 00:16:14,922
A LITTLE WHILE LONGER.

189
00:16:15,022 --> 00:16:20,588
-I'M NOT IN THE HABIT
OF CHANTING SUTRAS FOR THE DEAD.

190
00:16:20,688 --> 00:16:25,055
THE GODS AREN'T IN THE BUSINESS
OF SAVING ANYONE.

191
00:16:25,155 --> 00:16:28,488
ONLY YOU ARE RESPONSIBLE
FOR SAVING YOURSELF.

192
00:16:28,588 --> 00:16:29,655
YOU COULD FLEE.

193
00:16:29,755 --> 00:16:31,955
YOUR DEATH
WON'T CHANGE ANYTHING.

194
00:16:32,088 --> 00:16:35,488
BUT ALIVE, YOU MIGHT STILL
BE ABLE TO MAKE A DIFFERENCE.

195
00:16:35,588 --> 00:16:39,022
-YES. JUST A LITTLE LONGER.

196
00:16:39,122 --> 00:16:42,455
-LET'S DO THIS.

197
00:16:42,555 --> 00:16:43,422
-YES.

198
00:16:43,522 --> 00:16:46,222
I'VE TOYED WITH YOU ENOUGH.

199
00:16:46,322 --> 00:16:48,522
I'M NO LONGER AMUSED.

200
00:16:48,622 --> 00:16:51,622
[ GROANING ]

201
00:16:51,722 --> 00:16:56,522
AAH!

202
00:16:56,622 --> 00:16:58,322
-DID HE MEAN TO DO THAT?

203
00:16:58,422 --> 00:17:01,355
-HE'S BEEN IN THAT STATE
FOR TOO LONG.

204
00:17:01,455 --> 00:17:05,122
THE POWER'S STARTING TO BECOME
TOO MUCH FOR HIM TO CONTROL.

205
00:17:05,255 --> 00:17:07,122
-BUT IF THAT'S TRUE...

206
00:17:07,222 --> 00:17:07,955
-RIGHT.

207
00:17:08,055 --> 00:17:10,422
-[ GROANING ]

208
00:17:10,522 --> 00:17:11,888
-I DON'T KNOW.

209
00:17:11,988 --> 00:17:13,488
IT SEEMS SO CRUEL.

210
00:17:13,588 --> 00:17:16,888
-DRASTIC TIMES CALL
FOR DRASTIC MEASURES, MY FRIEND.

211
00:17:16,988 --> 00:17:19,588
-[ GROANING ]

212
00:17:26,955 --> 00:17:29,288
-BETTER LUCK...

213
00:17:29,388 --> 00:17:31,988
-...IN YOUR NEXT LIFE!

214
00:17:38,222 --> 00:17:39,688
-MIRA!

215
00:17:49,722 --> 00:17:51,588
-[ GASPS ]

216
00:17:54,055 --> 00:17:59,488
-HOMURA,
IT'S TIME TO SEE MY SON.

217
00:17:59,588 --> 00:18:03,122
MIR...

218
00:18:36,750 --> 00:18:41,450
-THIS FIELD -- I FEEL LIKE
I'VE BEEN IN THIS FIELD BEFORE.

219
00:18:41,550 --> 00:18:44,317
AND THERE'S
SOMETHING TERRIBLY FAMILIAR

220
00:18:44,417 --> 00:18:47,117
ABOUT THAT MOUNTAIN RANGE
OVER THERE.

221
00:18:47,217 --> 00:18:48,817
WHY DO I KNOW THIS PLACE?

222
00:18:48,917 --> 00:18:50,350
-SO, THAT'S IT.

223
00:19:02,117 --> 00:19:03,650
-YOU'RE HERE.

224
00:19:03,750 --> 00:19:06,017
-YOU SOUND SURPRISED.

225
00:19:06,117 --> 00:19:08,350
-HEY, HOMURA!

226
00:19:08,450 --> 00:19:10,184
I'LL NEVER ACCEPT THIS PLACE.

227
00:19:10,284 --> 00:19:11,650
YOU GOT THAT, SHITHEAD?

228
00:19:11,750 --> 00:19:12,650
-HMM.

229
00:19:12,750 --> 00:19:15,050
YOU HAVE NO CHOICE.

230
00:19:15,150 --> 00:19:20,150
-SO THIS IS
THE NEW HEAVEN AND EARTH.

231
00:19:20,250 --> 00:19:22,550
-WHY, YES, IT IS.

232
00:19:22,650 --> 00:19:24,717
DO YOU LIKE IT?

233
00:19:24,817 --> 00:19:27,517
NOT THAT IT MATTERS MUCH
WHAT YOU THINK.

234
00:19:27,617 --> 00:19:31,550
SOON THE OLD WILL HAVE TO
MAKE WAY FOR THE NEW.

235
00:19:31,650 --> 00:19:32,850
-THAT BOULDER.

236
00:19:32,950 --> 00:19:34,050
-THAT'S RIGHT.

237
00:19:34,150 --> 00:19:37,417
WHEN THE BOULDER REACHES
CRITICAL MASS,

238
00:19:37,517 --> 00:19:39,884
THE UNIVERSE WILL COLLAPSE
INTO A SINGULARITY

239
00:19:39,984 --> 00:19:42,284
THAT FORMS THE SEED
FOR THE NEW COSMOS.

240
00:19:42,384 --> 00:19:43,650
-THAT'S NOT NICE!

241
00:19:43,750 --> 00:19:46,817
-DO YOU HONESTLY THINK
THAT WE'LL LET THAT HAPPEN?

242
00:19:46,917 --> 00:19:48,284
YOU CAN'T BE THAT STUPID.

243
00:19:48,384 --> 00:19:50,917
-KEEP YOUR UNIVERSE
AND LEAVE OURS ALONE!

244
